{"task_id": "paint-house", "question_id": 256, "difficulty": "Medium", "tags": ["Array", "Dynamic Programming"], "problem_description": "There is a row of n houses, where each house can be painted one of three colors: red, blue, or green. The cost of painting each house with a certain color is different. You have to paint all the houses such that no two adjacent houses have the same color.\nThe cost of painting each house with a certain color is represented by an n x 3 cost matrix costs.\n\nFor example, costs[0][0] is the cost of painting house 0 with the color red; costs[1][2] is the cost of painting house 1 with color green, and so on...\n\nReturn the minimum cost to paint all houses.\n \nExample 1:\n\nInput: costs = [[17,2,17],[16,16,5],[14,3,19]]\nOutput: 10\nExplanation: Paint house 0 into blue, paint house 1 into green, paint house 2 into blue.\nMinimum cost: 2 + 5 + 3 = 10.\n\nExample 2:\n\nInput: costs = [[7,6,2]]\nOutput: 2\n\n \nConstraints:\n\ncosts.length == n\ncosts[i].length == 3\n1 <= n <= 100\n1 <= costs[i][j] <= 20\n\n", "starter_code": "class Solution:\n    def minCost(self, costs: List[List[int]]) -> int:\n        ", "completion": "class Solution:\n    def minCost(self, costs: List[List[int]]) -> int:\n        a = b = c = 0\n        for ca, cb, cc in costs:\n            a, b, c = min(b, c) + ca, min(a, c) + cb, min(a, b) + cc\n        return min(a, b, c)\n", "entry_point": "Solution().minCost", "test": "def check(candidate):\n    assert candidate(costs = [[11, 11, 13], [8, 12, 18], [9, 10, 3]]) == 22\n    assert candidate(costs = [[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6], [7, 8, 9]]) == 13\n    assert candidate(costs = [[7, 6, 2]]) == 2\n    assert candidate(costs = [[5, 8, 6], [19, 14, 13], [7, 5, 12]]) == 23\n    assert candidate(costs = [[17, 2, 17], [16, 16, 5], [14, 3, 19]]) == 10\n    assert candidate(costs = [[5, 8, 6], [19, 14, 13], [7, 5, 12], [14, 15, 17], [3, 20, 10]]) == 43\n    assert candidate(costs = [[3, 5, 3], [6, 17, 6], [7, 13, 18], [9, 10, 18]]) =